Here is a Knowledge Base (KB) article designed for External Vendor Managers. This guide provides step-by-step instructions on how to manage your team's access using the CyberArk Remote Access portal.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Vendor Manager Guide: Managing Your Team’s Access via CyberArk
Overview
You have been designated as a Vendor Manager for your organization. This role empowers you to invite, manage, and revoke access for your own team members who require connectivity to our systems.
Instead of waiting for our internal IT Help Desk to process individual requests, you can provision access for your staff directly. This "Delegated Administration" model ensures your team gets access quickly, while strictly adhering to the security boundaries defined by our organization.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Part 1: Prerequisites
Before inviting your team, ensure you have completed your own registration:
1. You must be registered: You should have already received an invitation, downloaded the CyberArk Mobile App, and registered your biometrics (FaceID/Fingerprint).
2. Vendor Manager Role: Confirm that you can see the "Team" or "Users" tab when you log into the Remote Access portal. If you do not see this, contact your internal sponsor to request the "Vendor Manager" role designation.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Part 2: How to Invite New Team Members
You can invite your colleagues to access the specific applications and systems assigned to your vendor group.
1. Log In to the Portal:
    ◦ Navigate to the Remote Access URL provided (e.g., https://portal.alero.io).
    ◦ Scan the QR code with your CyberArk Mobile App to log in.
2. Navigate to Team Management:
    ◦ Click on the Team or Users tab in the left-hand navigation menu.
3. Send Invitation:
    ◦ Click the "Invite" or "Add User" button.
    ◦ Enter the required details for your team member:
        ▪ First Name & Last Name
        ▪ Work Email Address
        ▪ Mobile Phone Number (Required for SMS verification)
4. Set Access Timeframe (Optional):
    ◦ Depending on the permissions granted to you, you may need to define the access window (e.g., "Oct 1st to Oct 31st").
    ◦ Note: You cannot grant access beyond the expiry date of your own account or the project scope defined by our internal administrators.
5. Confirm and Send:
    ◦ Click Invite. The system will automatically send an email to your colleague with activation instructions.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Part 3: The Onboarding Experience (What Your Team Needs to Do)
Once you send the invite, your team member must complete the setup themselves. They cannot share accounts; each user must have their own unique biometric identity.
Please instruct your team to follow these steps:
1. Check Email: Look for the invitation email (check Spam/Junk folders if missing).
2. Download App: Install the CyberArk Mobile App on their smartphone (iOS or Android).
3. Register: Open the app, enter their phone number, and register their biometrics (FaceID or Fingerprint).
4. Activate: Click the link in the invitation email to bind their app to our tenant.
Crucial Security Note: Access is password-less. Your team members do not need to create a username or password. Their physical smartphone and biometrics act as their key.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Part 4: Managing and Monitoring Your Team
As a Vendor Manager, you are responsible for maintaining the accuracy of your team list.
Monitoring Status
In the Team tab, you can view the status of every user you have invited:
• Invited / Pending: The email was sent, but the user has not yet registered. You may need to "Resend Invite" if they lost the email.
• Active: The user has successfully registered and can access the system.
Offboarding (Revoking Access)
If a team member leaves your company or moves to a different project, you must remove their access immediately to maintain security.
1. Locate the user in the Team list.
2. Select the user and click Delete or Deactivate.
3. Result: Their access is immediately revoked. Even if they have the app, they will no longer be able to scan the QR code to log in to our environment.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)
Q: Can I grant my team access to additional servers? A: No. You can only invite users to the groups assigned to you. If your team needs access to new systems, please contact your internal Project Manager to update the scope of your Vendor Group.
Q: Does my team need a VPN? A: No. CyberArk Remote Access is clientless and VPN-less. Your team only needs a web browser (HTML5) and the mobile app to connect.
Q: What if a team member loses their phone? A: For security reasons, if a device is lost, that user's specific access token is compromised (though it still requires biometrics). You should Deactivate their user immediately in the portal. When they get a new phone, send them a fresh invitation to register the new device.
Q: Why does the invite expire? A: Invitations are time-sensitive to prevent unauthorized usage. If a team member waits too long (typically 24-48 hours) to accept, the link will expire, and you will need to resend the invitation.
